==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Greek '''ataxiā''' meaning "disorder", derived from '''ataktós''' meaning "disorderly"

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}} 
'''ataxia'''
# {{pathology}} unsteady and clumsy motion of the [[limb]]s or [[trunk]] due to a failure of the fine coordination of [[muscle]] movements.

